reviews.review_text: Belts Good recording,good energy,great set list,peggy-o,loser,terrapin,baby blue,oh my!
you could smell the wool sweaters pathchouli and early spring in Upstate New York.  Loved this show for a long time.  Hot show

If any recording deserves 5 stars... ...it's this one!

So far, no matrix, thank God!

Thanks to Rick, Muletaper and Jamie W.

fun memories, sounds great No, I didn't go to this show, but I had the first set on cassette back in the Maxell 90 minute days.   Played it lots. Funny how random it seemed what you came across then, as opposed to being so lucky now as to essentially choose from everything ever captured at the click of some buttons.  Anyway, this sounds great, and the playing exceeds the setlist in the first set (even though the setlist is just fine to begin with.)  I think I am listening to the second set for the first time, and its very good so far...  Thanks!
